  "chapter": {
    "number": 41,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God’s Help to Israel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Be silent before Me, O islands,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2654
          },
          {
            "text": "and let the peoples renew their strength.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Let them come forward and testify;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let us together draw near for judgment.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who has aroused one from the east",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and called him to his feet in righteousness",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2655
          },
          {
            "text": "?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He hands nations over to him",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and subdues kings before him.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He turns them to dust with his sword,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to windblown chaff with his bow.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He pursues them, going on safely,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "hardly touching the path with his feet.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who has performed this and carried it out,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "calling forth the generations from the beginning?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I, the LORD—the first and the last—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I am He.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The islands see and fear;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the ends of the earth tremble.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They approach and come forward.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Each one helps the other",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and says to his brother, “Be strong!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The craftsman encourages the goldsmith,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and he who wields the hammer",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "cheers him who strikes the anvil,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "saying of the welding, “It is good.”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He nails it down so it will not be toppled.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“But you, O Israel, My servant,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Jacob, whom I have chosen,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "descendant of Abraham My friend—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I brought you from the ends of the earth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and called you from its farthest corners.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I said, ‘You are My servant.’",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have chosen and not rejected you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not fear, for I am with you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not be afraid, for I am your God.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will strengthen you; I will surely help you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will uphold you with My right hand of righteousness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, all who rage against you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will be ashamed and disgraced;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "those who contend with you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will be reduced to nothing and will perish.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will seek them but will not find them.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Those who wage war against you will come to nothing.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I am the LORD your God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who takes hold of your right hand",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and tells you: Do not fear,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will help you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not fear, O worm of Jacob,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O few men of Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will help you,” declares the LORD.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Your Redeemer is the Holy One of Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, I will make you into a threshing sledge,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "new and sharp, with many teeth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You will thresh the mountains and crush them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and reduce the hills to chaff.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will winnow them, and a wind will carry them away;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a gale will scatter them.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "But you will rejoice in the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will glory in the Holy One of Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The poor and needy seek water, but there is none;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their tongues are parched with thirst.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I, the LORD, will answer them;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I, the God of Israel, will not forsake them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will open rivers on the barren heights,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and fountains in the middle of the valleys.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will turn the desert into a pool of water,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the dry land into flowing springs.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will plant cedars in the wilderness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "acacias, myrtles, and olive trees.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will set cypresses",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2656
          },
          {
            "text": "in the desert,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "elms and boxwood together,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "so that all may see and know,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "may consider and understand,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "that the hand of the LORD has done this",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the Holy One of Israel has created it.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Meaningless Idols"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Present your case,” says the LORD.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Submit your arguments,” says the King of Jacob.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Let them come and tell us what will happen.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Tell the former things,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so that we may reflect on them and know the outcome.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Or announce to us what is coming.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Tell us the things that are to come,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that we may know that you are gods.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Yes, do something good or evil,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that we may look on together in dismay.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, you are nothing",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your work is of no value.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Anyone who chooses you is detestable.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I have raised up one from the north, and he has come—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "one from the east who calls on My name.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He will march over rulers as if they were mortar,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a potter who treads the clay.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who has declared this from the beginning,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that we may know,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and from times past,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that we may say: ‘He was right’?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "No one announced it, no one foretold it,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no one heard your words.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I was the first to tell Zion:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2657
          },
          {
            "text": "‘Look, here they are!’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "And I gave to Jerusalem",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a herald of good news.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When I look, there is no one;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there is no counselor among them;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "when I ask them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they have nothing to say.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "See, they are all a delusion;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their works amount to nothing;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "their images are as empty as the wind.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
